Mexican Rice with Chicken

1 lb chicken
2 tbsp cooking oil
1/2 cup whole grain rice
1 can peeled tomatoes
1 Tbsp chicken bouillon
3 Cups water
1 cup onion, chopped
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 tsp salt
1/4 tsp pepper
1 cup frozen peas

Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt.  
In 12 in. skillet brown chiken in hot oil about 15 minutes.  
Remove from pan.  
In drippings remaining, cook rice, onion and garlic till rice is golden.  
Add water, tomatoes (blend if desigered) bouillion, salt and pepper .  
Bring to boil and return chicken to pan, cover and simmer 30 - 35 minutes or till chicken is tender.  
Add peas; Cover and cook 5 minutes more.




